# Saleor Platform - Cursor IDE Rules

## Primary Reference
Always refer to AGENTS.md in the repository root for:
- Container restart guidelines
- Build/lint/test commands
- Code style guidelines
- App-specific patterns
- Docker workflow
- Apps overview and features

## Workspace Structure
This is a multi-project workspace:
- `saleor/` - Django/GraphQL backend (Python)
- `dashboard/` - Admin dashboard (React + Vite, TypeScript)
- `storefront/` - Next.js storefront (TypeScript)
- `apps/` - Saleor Apps monorepo (Next.js + TypeScript, Turborepo)
- `infra/` - Docker compose and setup scripts

## Environment-Specific Rules
Check for `.cursorrules` files in:
- `saleor/` for Python/Django rules
- `dashboard/` for React/TypeScript rules
- `storefront/` for Next.js rules
- `apps/` for monorepo/Next.js app rules

## Key Principles
- Always determine which Docker container needs restarting after changes (see AGENTS.md Container Restart Guidelines)
- Follow existing patterns in the target package (do not mix styles)
- Keep edits minimal and localized; avoid wide refactors without request
- Never add emojis to source code unless explicitly requested
- Use appropriate build/lint/test commands for each project (see AGENTS.md Build/Lint/Test Commands)
- Respect existing patterns in the directory you are working in

## Docker Development Workflow
- All services run in containers via Docker Compose
- Use `docker compose -f infra/docker-compose.dev.yml restart <container-name>` to restart containers
- Check AGENTS.md for specific container restart requirements based on what changed
- View logs: `docker compose -f infra/docker-compose.dev.yml logs -f <container-name>`

## Code Style
- Python (saleor/): Black-style formatting, Ruff linting, type hints required
- TypeScript (dashboard/, storefront/, apps/): Prettier formatting, ESLint rules, avoid `any`
- Follow language-specific conventions in AGENTS.md Code Style Guidelines section

## When in Doubt
- Prefer the closest existing pattern in the directory you touch
- Ask for clarification if a change might affect multiple packages
- Refer to AGENTS.md for detailed guidance on specific technologies
